Opgave 3

Find the driving point impedance seen by the voltage source in Figure P11â3 and the voltage transfer function T_V(s) = V_2(s) / V_1(s).

Driving point impedans:

Dette er simpelt - hvad er \(V_1(s)\) ?

\[ V_1(s)= V_L + V_R + V_C \]

Omskrevet:

\[ V_1(s)= I(s)\left( L s + R + \frac{1}{Cs}\right) \]

Dermed:

\[ \frac{V_1(s)}{I(s)}= L s + R + \frac{1}{Cs} \]

Omskrevet:

\[ Z(s)=\frac{V_1(s)}{I(s)}= \frac{LCs^2 + RCs +1}{Cs} \]

Transfer function:

Da det er en spÃ¦ndingsdeler gÃ¦lder flg.:

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{R}{Ls + \frac{1}{Cs}+R} \]

Omskrevet:

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{R}{\frac{LCs^2 + RCs +1}{Cs}} \]

\[ \boxed{ T_V(s)=\frac{RCs}{LCs^2 + RCs +1} } \]

Opgave 5

Find the driving point impedance seen by the voltage source in Figure P11â5 and the voltage transfer function T_V(s) = V_2(s)/V_1(s).

Driving pointe impedance \(Z_i\)

Vi har:

\[ -V_1(s) + I_1(s) \cdot\left( R + \frac{1}{Cs}||L s\right) = 0 \]

Dermed:

\[ Z_i(s) = \frac{V_1(s)}{I_1(s)} = R + \frac{\frac{1}{Cs}\cdot Ls}{\frac{1}{Cs} + Ls} \]

\[ Z_i(s) = \frac{V_1(s)}{I_1(s)} = \left(\frac{1}{Ls}\cdot Cs\right)^{-1} + R \]

Dette kan omskrives til:

\[ \frac{CLRs^2+Ls+R}{CLs^2+1} \]

Voltage transfer function \(T_v(s)\)

Std. spÃ¦ndingsdeler formel:

\[ V_2(s) = V_1(s) \cdot \frac{\frac{1}{Cs}||Ls}{R+\frac{1}{Cs}||Ls} = V_1(s) \cdot \frac{Ls}{R\left(CLs^2+1\right)+Ls} \]

Dermed:

\[ T_v(s) = \frac{V_2(s)}{V_1(s)} = \frac{Ls}{R\left(CLs^2+1\right)+Ls} = \frac{Ls}{CLRs^2+Ls+R} \]

Resultater:

\[ \boxed{ Z_i(s) = \frac{CLRs^2+Ls+R}{CLs^2+1} \; \mathrm{\Omega} } \] \[ \boxed{ \; T_v(s) = \frac{Ls}{CLRs^2+Ls+R} } \]

ForsÃ¸g med vÃ¦rdier.

\[ R = 1000\;\mathrm{\Omega} \quad L = 1\;\mathrm{H} \quad C = 1\mathrm{ÂµF} \]

\[ Z_i(s) = \frac{10^3\left(s^2+10^3s+10^6\right)}{s^2+10^6} \; \mathrm{\Omega} \]

\[ \; T_v(s) = \frac{10^3s}{s^2+10^3s+10^6} \]

Driving point impedans

Transfer function.

Det er en non-inverterende opstilling - derfor gÃ¦lder flg.:

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} \] Hvor: \[ Z_1 = 2R \quad Z_2 = 2R||C \] \[ Z_2 = \frac{2R \cdot \frac{1}{Cs}}{2R+\frac{1}{Cs}} \] Derfor: \[ T_V(s)=\frac{2R+\frac{2R\frac{1}{Cs}}{2R+\frac{1}{Cs}}}{\frac{2R\frac{1}{Cs}}{2R+\frac{1}{Cs}}} \]

Omskrevet: \[ \boxed{ T_V(s)=2RCs+2 } \]

Med vÃ¦rdierne: \(R = 100\;\mathrm{\Omega} \quad C = 0.01\mathrm{ÂµF}\):

Opgave 11

Find the voltage transfer function T_V(s) = V_2(s) / V_1(s) in Figure P11â11. Select values of R and C so that T_V(s) has a pole at s = -100 krad/s.

Voltage transfer function \(T_v(s)\)

Da det er en ikke-inverterende operationsforstÃ¦rker gÃ¦lder flg: \[ V_2 = V_1 \cdot \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} \]

Hvor:

\[ Z_1 = R||C \quad Z_2 = R \]

Dermed:

\[ T_v(s) ) \frac{\left(\frac{1}{R}+Cs\right)^1+R}{R} = \frac{RCs+2}{RCs+1} = \frac{s + \frac{2}{RC}}{s+\frac{1}{RC}} \]

Poler i systemet.

For at fÃ¥ en pol i \(-100k\;\mathrm{rad/s}\) kigges i nÃ¦vneren: \(s + \frac{1}{RC}\) - hvilket viser at der findes en pol i \(\frac{-1}{RC}\).

Derfor:

R vÃ¦lges: \[ R = 100 \;\mathrm{\Omega} \] C findes: \[ -100.000 = \frac{-1}{100\cdot C} \to C = 100\mathrm{nF} \]

Opgave 13

Find the current transfer function T_I(s) = I_2(s)/I_1(s) in Figure P11â13. Select values of R and L so that T_I(s) has a pole at s = - 377 rad/s

Dette er en std. strÃ¸mdeler.

Derfor gÃ¦lder:

\[ T_I(s) = \frac{I_2(s)}{I_1(s)} = \frac{Y_2(s)}{Y_1(s)+Y_2(s)} \]

Hvor: \[ Y_1 = \frac{1}{R} \quad \frac{1}{Y_2 = Ls + 2R} \]

Dette giver:

\[ \frac{I_2(s)}{I_1(s)} = \frac{\frac{1}{Y_2 = Ls + 2R}}{\frac{1}{R}+\frac{1}{Y_2 = Ls + 2R}} \]

En omskrivning giver:

\[ \frac{Y_2(s)}{Y_1(s)+Y_2(s)} = \frac{Z_1(s)}{Z_1(s)+Z_2(s)} \]

Derfor:

\[ T_I(s)= \frac{R}{3R+Ls} = \frac{\frac{R}{L}}{\frac{3R}{L}+s} \]

Dette giver en pol i \(-\frac{3R}{L}\;\mathrm{rad/s}\).

Polen i -377â¦

Der vÃ¦lges en modstand: \(4k7\Omega\).

Derfor:

\(-377 = -\frac{3\cdot 4k7}{L} \to L =\frac{3 \dot 4k7}{377} = 37.4 \;\mathrm{H}\)

\[ T_I(s)= \frac{\frac{4k7\Omega}{37.4\;\mathrm{H}}}{\frac{3\cdot4k7\Omega}{37.4\;\mathrm{H}}+s} \]

Opgave 15

Find the voltage transfer function T_V(s) = V_2(s)/V_1(s) of the cascade connection in Figure P11â15. Locate the poles and zeros of the transfer function

Transfer function

KomponentID:

\(C_1 = 0.047 \mu F \;\) \(C_2 = 0.1 \mu F \;\)

\(R_1 = 22k\Omega\;\) \(R_2 = 1k\Omega \;\) \(R_3 = 10k\Omega \;\)

Venstresiden

Denne del af kredslÃ¸bet er en spÃ¦ndingsdeler bestÃ¥ende af \(C_1\) og \(R_1\)

\[ v_1(t) = \frac{R_1}{R_1+C_1} \]

Laplacetransformationen giver: \[ T_{Vdivider}(s) = \frac{R_1}{R_1+\frac{1}{C_1s}} \]

HÃ¸jresiden

OperationsforstÃ¦rkeren er koblet som en ikke inverterende forstÃ¦rker. Derfor: \[ T_{Vopamp}(s) = \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} \]

Hvor: \[ Z_1 = R_3 \quad Z_2 = \frac{1}{C_2s}+R_2 \]

Dermed:

\[ T_{Vopamp}(s)=\frac{R_3+\frac{1}{C_2s}+R_2}{\frac{1}{C_2s}+R_2} \]

Med de rigtige vÃ¦rdier indsat:

\[ T_{Vdivider}(s)= \frac{22k\Omega}{22k\Omega+\frac{1}{0.047\mu F s}} = \frac{s}{s+967.1} \\ T_{Vopamp}(s)=\frac{10k\Omega+\frac{1}{0.1 \mu F s}+1k\Omega }{\frac{1}{0.1 \mu F s}+1k\Omega } = \frac{11(s+909.1)}{s+10000} \]

Hvorfor:

\[ T_V(s) = T_{Vdivider}(s) \cdot T_{Vopamp}(s) \]

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{C_1 R_1 s \cdot(C_2(R_2+R_2)s+1)}{(C_2R_2s+1)(C_1R_1s+1)} \]

\[ T_V(s) = \frac{s}{s+967.1} \cdot \frac{11(s+909.1)}{s+10000} \]

\[ \boxed{ T_V(s) = \frac{11s(s+909.1)}{(s+967.1)(s+10000)} } \] Det ses at funktionen har Ã©t nulpunkt: \(Z_1 = -909.1 \; rad/s\)

Desuden er der to poler: \(p_1 = -967.1\; rad/s \quad p_2 = -10000\; rad/s\)

Opgave 17

Find the impulse response at v_2(t) in Figure P11â17. Find the circuitâs step response.

Transfer function

Da det er en spÃ¦ndingsdeler gÃ¸r flg. sig gÃ¦ldende - efter en laplacetransformation:

\[V_2(s) = V_1(s)\;\cdot\; \frac{R_2+\frac{1}{Cs}}{R_1+R_2+\frac{1}{Cs}}\]

Omskrevet1: \[\underset{Y(s)}{\underbrace{V_2(s)}} = \underset{X(s)}{\underbrace{V_1(s)}}\;\cdot\; \underset{T_V(s) \; \lor \; H(s)}{\underbrace{\frac{R_2Cs+1}{R_1Cs+R_2Cs+1}}} \]

Transfer function

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{R_2Cs+1}{R_1Cs+R_2Cs+1} \]

KomponentID:

\[ R_1 = 33k\Omega\\ R_2 = 47k\Omega\\ C = 0.15 \mu F \]

\[ T_V(s)=\frac{47k\Omega \cdot 0.15 \mu F \cdot s+1}{33k\Omega \cdot0.15 \mu F s+47k\Omega \cdot 0.15 \mu F s+1} = \frac{0.5875\cdot(s+141.8)}{s+83.33} \] Her ses det at et enkelt nulpunkt er at finde \(z_1 = -141.8 \; rad/s\) og en enkelt pol \(p_1 = -83.33 \; rad/s\)

Impulserespons

Ved at gÃ¸re fÃ¸lgende: \[ v_{impulse}(t)= \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ T_V(s) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{0.5875\cdot(s+141.8)}{s+83.33} \right\} \] Dette giver: \[ \boxed{ v_{impulse}(t) = 0.5785 \cdot \left(\delta(t)+58.47e^{-83.33t}\right)\cdot u(t) }\]

Steprespons

Ved at gÃ¸re fÃ¸lgende:

\[ v_{step}(t)=\mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{1}{s} \cdot H(s) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{1}{s} \cdot T_V(s) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ \frac{0.5875\cdot(s+141.8)}{s^2+83.33s} \right\} \]

Dette giver:

\[ \boxed{ v_{step}(t) = (0.5875\cdot(1.702-0.702e^{-83.33t}))\cdot u(t) } \]

Driving point impedans

Vi har fÃ¸lgende KVL loop:

\[ v_1(t)=v_r+v_r+v_c \] Dette laplace transformeres:

\[ \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_1(t) \right\} = \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_{R1}(t) \right\} + \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_{R2}(t) \right\} + \mathcal{L}^{-1}\left\{ v_C(t) \right\} \]

og giver: \[ V_1(s) = V_{R1}(s)+V_{R2}(s)+V_C(s) \]

En let omskrivning

\[ V_1(s)= I(s)(R_1+R_2)+ \frac{1}{Cs} I(s) \]

Dermed:

\[ \frac{V_1(s)}{I(s)} = R_1+R_2 + \frac{1}{Cs} \]

og vi har driving point impedansen:

\[ Z(s) = \frac{CR_1s+CR_2s+1}{Cs} \]

og vi har driving point impedansen / med vÃ¦rdier!: \[ \boxed{ Z(s) = \frac{80000\cdot(s+83.33)}{s} } \]

Opgave 34

The circuit in Figure P11â34 is in the steady state with v1(t) = 5 cos 1414.21t V. Find v2_SS(t). Repeat for v1(t) = 5cos 1 kt V. And without doing any calculations, repeat for v_1(t) = 5 V.

Vi har:

\[ v_{1ss}(t) = 5 \cos(1414.21t) \]

Dette giver: \[ v_A = 5 \quad \omega = 1414.21 \]

Transfer funktionen der pÃ¥virker systemet:

\[ T_v(s) = \frac{Ls+\frac{1}{Cs}}{R+Ls+\frac{1}{Cs}} \]

Med vÃ¦rdier:

\[ T_v(s) = \frac{25\;\mathrm{mH}s+\frac{1}{20\;\mathrm{ÂµF}s}}{100\;\mathrm{\Omega}+25\;\mathrm{mH}s+\frac{1}{20\;\mathrm{ÂµF}s}} = \frac{s^2+2\cdot10^6}{s^2+4\cdot10^3s+2\cdot10^6} \]

Omskrivning til frekvensdomÃ¦net:

\[ T_v(\omega j) = \frac{\omega j^2+2\cdot10^6}{\omega j^2+4\cdot10^3\omega j+2\cdot10^6} \]

\[ \angle T_v(s) = \arctan\left( \frac{4000\omega}{\omega^2-2\cdot 10^6} \right) \]

Derfor kan fÃ¸lgende opskrives:

\[ v_{2ss}= v_A |T_v(\omega j)|\cos(\omega t + \phi + \angle{T(j\omega)})\; \mathrm{V} \]

AltsÃ¥: \[ v_{2ss}= 5 \cdot |T_v(\omega j)| \cdot \cos(1414.21 t + \angle{T(j\omega)})\; \mathrm{V} \]

Med \(\omega = 1414.21\) \[ |T_v(s)| = 1.781\cdot 10^{-6} \quad \angle T_v(s) = -90 \] \[ v_{2ss}= 5\cdot 1.781\cdot 10^{-6} \cdot \cos(1414.21 t -90) = 8.91\cos(1414.21-90)\; \mathrm{ÂµV} \]

Med \(\omega = 1000\) \[ |T_v(s)| = 242.5\cdot 10^{-3} \quad \angle T_v(s) = -76.96 \] \[ v_{2ss}= 5\cdot 242.5\cdot 10^{-3} \cdot \cos(1000 t -76.96) = 1.213\cos(1000-76.96)\; \mathrm{ÂµV} \]

Opgave 70

\[ Z_2 = s \quad Z_1 = s+4000+\frac{4000000}{s}-s = 4000+\frac{4000000}{s} \]

\[ Z_2 = 1H \quad Z_1 = 4k\Omega + \frac{1}{4000000} = 4k\Omega + 250\;\mathrm{nF} \]

SpÃ¦ndingsdeler: \[ T_v(s) = \frac{Z_2}{Z_1+Z_2} \]

Omskaleret sÃ¥ \(L < 50mH\)

\[ Z_2\cdot k = 50mH \to k = 0.050 \] \[ Z_1 \cdot k = 4 k\Omega \cdot 0.05 + 250\;\mathrm{nF}\cdot \frac{1}{0.05} \]

Derfor:

SpÃ¦ndingsdeler: \[ T_v(s) = \frac{Z_2}{Z_1+Z_2} \] Hvor

\[ \boxed{ Z_1 = 200\Omega + 5\;\mathrm{ÂµF} \qquad Z_2 = 50\;\mathrm{mH} } \]

Funktionen vist som spÃ¦ndingdeler.

\[ R_1 = 62.5\Omega \quad R_2 = 187.5 \Omega \quad C_1 = 160ÂµF \quad C_2 = 32ÂµF \quad L_1 = 100mH \]

\[ V_2(s) = V_1(s) \cdot \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} \]

\[ \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} \]

\[ \frac{Z_1+Z_2}{Z_2} = \pm \frac{s+625+\frac{62500}{s}}{s+1250+\frac{250000}{s}} \]

\[ Z_2 = -(s + 625 + \frac{1}{62500}) =-(1H + 625 \Omega + 16ÂµF) \]

\[ Z_1 = s + 1250 + \frac{1}{250000} - Z_2= 2H + 1875 \Omega + 20ÂµF \]
